=== Patient CA-A ===

This patient was a 61 year old male with a metastatic ''RET-KIF5B'' fusion positive NSCLC. After failure of Carboplatin, Pemetrexed, and Pembrolizumab followed by the multi kinase inhibitor Lenvatinib, he then received compassionate access to the RET tyrosine kinase inhibitor Selpercatinib ([[#fig:ca99timeline|[fig:ca99timeline]]]). He experienced almost immediate improvement following Selpercatinib with decreased levels of carcinoembryonic antigen and almost 100% reduction of ''RET'' fusion positive ctDNA after one month ([[#fig:ca99ctDNA|[fig:ca99ctDNA]]]). Similar to the ctDNA analysis, Positron emission tomography (PET) and computed tomography (CT) imaging revealed significantly reduced tracer uptake in multiple sites and partial response to treatment ([[#fig:ca99pet|[fig:ca99pet]]]).

