In keeping with the small cell transformation, we could highlight an intronic ''TP53'' mutations, which was present at almost 100% VAF in all autopsy samples. However, the same variant was also found in the diagnostic sample, which was reportedly adenocarcinoma. The variant was therefore not sufficient to drive the transformation, but could have been a predisposition for the patient ([[#fig:ca51heatmap|[fig:ca51heatmap]]]).

